x\n| length2         = 5:25\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side two\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| note1           = Ultimate Club Vocal Mix\n| length1         = 6:10\n| title2          = I.O.U.\n| note2           = Ultimate Club Dub Mix\n| length2         = 6:35\n}}\n\n== Chart performance ==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (1983)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|Australian [[Kent Music Report]]<ref name=kentmusicreport83>{{cite book|last=Kent|first=David|title=Australian Chart Book 1970-1992|isbn=0-646-11917-6}}</ref> \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|-\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=chartstats83/> \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n|Dutch [[GfK]] chart<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dutchcharts.nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Freeez&titel=I.+O.+U.&cat=s |title=dutchcharts.nl - Freeez - I. O. U. |accessdate=31 July 2009|language=nl}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n|[[Dutch Top 40]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.top40.nl/index.aspx?week=33&jaar=1983 |title=De Nederlandse Top 40 - week 33, 1983  |accessdate=31 July 2009|language=nl}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2\n|-\n|[[Irish Singles Chart]]<ref name=irishcharts>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishcharts.ie/search/placement |title=irishcharts.ie search results |access-date=31 July 2009 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/5hFf8iFDu?url=http://www.irishcharts.ie/search/placement |archive-date=3 June 2009 |df= }}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n|[[South African Singles Charts]]<ref name=http://www.rock.co.za/files/springbok_top_20_(F).html /> \n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|3\n|-\n|[[Swedish Singles Chart]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://swedishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Freeez&titel=I.+O.+U.&cat=s |title=swedishcharts.com - Freeez - I. O. U. |accessdate=31 July 2009}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|12\n|-\n|[[Swiss Singles Chart]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://hitparade.ch/showitem.asp?interpret=Freeez&titel=I.+O.+U.&cat=s |title=Freeez - I. O. U. - hitparade.ch |accessdate=31 July 2009|language=de}}</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|5\n|-\n|US [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs|''Billboard'' Black Singles]]<ref name=allmusic/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|13\n|-\n|US [[Hot Dance Club Songs|''Billboard'' Club Play Singles]]<ref name=allmusic/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|1\n|-\n|[[Media Control Charts|West German Singles Chart]]<ref>[http://ki.informatik.uni-wuerzburg.de/~topsi/deu1983/deu_1983t.html German Top 20 - The Chart of 1983]</ref>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|8\n|-\n!Chart (1987)\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=chartstats87/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|23\n|-\n|[[Irish Singles Chart]]<ref name=irishcharts/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|26\n|-\n|US [[Hot Dance Singles Sales|''Billboard'' Hot Dance Music/Maxi-Singles Sales]]<ref name=allmusic/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|37\n|-\n|US [[Hot Dance Club Play|''Billboard'' Hot Dance Music/Club Play]]<ref name=allmusic/>\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|18\n|}\n\n== Personnel ==\n* [[John Rocca]] \u2013 [[singing|vocals]], hand percussion, [[Bongo drum|bongos]], [[conga]]s\n* Everton McCalla \u2013 [[drum kit|drums]], vocals\n* Tina B \u2013 vocals\n* Andy Stennett \u2013 [[piano]]\n* [[Fred Zarr]] \u2013 piano\n* Cosa \u2013 bongos, congas\n* [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]] \u2013 [[songwriter|music and lyrics]], [[record producer|production]], [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mix]], [[remix]]\n* [[John \"Jellybean\" Benitez]] \u2013 mix\n* [[John Robie]] \u2013 mix, remix\n\n;additional personnel for 1986/87 versions\n* Richard Scher \u2013 co-production\n* Graeme Durham \u2013 editor\n* Tim Palmer \u2013 editor\n* Arthur Baker \u2013 remix\n* Jay Burnett \u2013 remix\n* John Rocca \u2013 remix\n* Latin Rascals \u2013 remix\n* Raul Soto \u2013 remix\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Freeez}}\n\n[[Category:1983 singles]]\n[[Category:1987 singles]]\n[[Category:Freeez songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Dance Club Songs number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Arthur Baker (musician)]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Arthur Baker (musician)]]\n[[Category:Beggars Banquet Records singles]]\n[[Category:1983 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name        = I.O.U.\n| cover       = Freeez IOU single cover.jpg\n| alt         =\n| type        = single\n| artist      = [[Freeez]]\n| album       = [[Gonna Get You]]\n| B-side      = {{ubl|\"I Dub U\"|\"We Got the Jazz\"}}\n| released    = June 17, 1983\n| format      = [[7\" vinyl]], [[12-inch single|12\" vinyl]], [[CD single|CD]] (1987)\n| recorded    = 1983, [[Unique Recording Studios]], [[New York City]]\n| studio      =\n| venue       =\n| genre       = {{flatlist|\n*[[Electro (music)|Electro]]\n*[[Freestyle music|freestyle]]\n*[[synthpop]]\n}}\n| length      = 7:50 (12\" version)<br />3:49 (7\" version)\n| label       = [[Beggars Banquet Records|Beggars Banquet]] (UK)<br />Streetwise (US),<br />[[Victor Entertainment|Victor Industries]] (JP),<br />[[Virgin records|Virgin]] (Germany),<br />[[Vertigo Records|Vertigo]] (Canada),<br />Criminal (US, 1986),<br />Citybeat (UK, 1987)\n| writer      = [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]]\n| producer    = [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]]\n| prev_title  = [[One to One (song)|One to One]]\n| prev_year   = 1982\n| next_title  = [[Pop Goes My Love/Scratch Goes My Dub|Pop Goes My Love\n| next_title  = Scratch Goes My Dub]]\n| next_year   = 1983\n| misc        = {{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Freeez]]\n | type       = single\n | prev_title = Train of Thoughts\n | prev_year  = 1985\n | title      = \"I.O.U.\"<br />(remix)\n | year       = 1987\n | next_title = \"[[Southern Freeez (song)|Southern Freeez]]\"<br />(remix)\n | next_year  = 1987\n}}\n}}\n\n\"'''I.O.U.'''\" is a song from 1983 by [[United Kingdom|British]] musical group [[Freeez]], their most successful hit. The song \"IOU\", was written & produced by [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]] and remixed by [[Jellybean Benitez]] & [[Arthur Baker (musician)|Arthur Baker]].\n\nThe song was an international hit. The record scored #2 in the [[UK Singles Chart]]<ref name=chartstats83>{{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/Warriors |title=The Official Charts Company - Freeez - IOU |accessdate=31 July 2009}}</ref> earlier in 1983 before reaching the top of the [[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']] [[Hot Dance Club Play]] chart in the U.S.,<ref name=allmusic>{{cite web |url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p17700/charts-awards|pure_url=yes}} |title=Freeez > Charts & Awards > Billboard Singles |publisher=[[allmusic]] |accessdate=31 July 2009}}</ref> giving them their only chart-topping single on any chart in America. It then became the 20th best-selling single of 1983 in the United Kingdom. \"I.O.U.\" was used for the 1984 [[breakdance]] [[film|movie]], ''[[Beat Street]]''. The chorus is often erroneously sung by listeners as \"A-E, A-E I-O-U, and sometimes Y\", referring to the vowels of the alphabet. It is actually \"A-E, A-E, I-O-U, U, I sometimes cry\" and \"A-E, A-E, I-O-U, U, I sometimes lie\".\n\nDuring 1986 a 12\" single was released in the US by the Criminal Records company, with new remixes. Some of these remixes were given a re-release during 1987 in the UK for the Citybeat label as \"I.O.U. (The Ultimate Mixes '87)\", however, it only scored #23 in the UK Singles Chart this time.<ref name=chartstats87>{{cite web |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/search/singles/Want%20To%20Make%20The%20World%20Turn%20Around |title=The Official Charts Company - Freeez - IOU 1987 |accessdate=31 July 2009}}</ref>\n\n==Samples==\nThe song has been sampled multiple times. [[Cutfather]] and Joe used a sample for their [[remix]] of [[Brandy Norwood|Brandy]]'s 2002 single \"[[Full Moon (Brandy Norwood song)|Full Moon]]\"; [[Cheryl Cole]] for the song \"Let's Get Down\" from her 2010 album ''[[Messy Little Raindrops]]'' as does Wawa for the remix of [[StoneBridge (DJ)|StoneBridge]]'s 2007 single ''S.O.S''. [[Jamie xx]] uses a vocal sample for the song \"Girl\", which closes his debut solo album ''[[In Colour (Jamie xx album)|In Colour]]''.\n\n== Track listings ==\n\n=== 1983 releases ===\n;7\" vinyl\n* UK: Beggars Banquet / BEG 96\n* Germany, Netherlands: Virgin / 105 535\n* US: Streetwise / SWRL-1110\n* Australia: Powderworks / POW 0146\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side one\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| length1         = 3:48\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side two\n| title1          = I Dub U\n| length1         = 4:38\n}}\n\n* Japan: Victor / VIPX-1742\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side one\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| length1         =\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side two\n| title1          = [[Pop Goes My Love/Scratch Goes My Dub|Pop Goes My Love]]\n| length1         =\n}}\n\n;12\" vinyl\n* UK: Beggars Banquet / BEG 96(T)\n* Germany, France: Virgin / 600 902\n* Australia: Powderworks / POWT 0146\n* Spain: Beggars Banquet / F-600902\n* Canada: Vertigo / SOVX 2327\n\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side one\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| note1           = Megamix\n| length1         = 8:43\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side two\n| title1          = I Dub U\n| length1         = 7:37\n| title2          = We Got the Jazz\n| length2         = 4:04\n}}\n\n* UK: Beggars Banquet / BEG 96TA\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side one\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| note1           = Megamix\n| length1         = 8:43\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side two\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| note1           = Accapella Mix\n| length1         = 4:03\n| title2          = We Got the Jazz\n| length2         = 4:04\n}}\n\n* US: Streetwise / SWRL 2210 (some with second track on side two)\n{{tracklist\n| headline        = Side one\n| title1          = I.O.U.\n| note1           =\n| length1         = 7:50\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| headline