{"title_page": "Klaus Huhn", "text_new": "{{expand language|topic=|langcode=de|otherarticle=Klaus Huhn|date=July 2015}}\n[[File:Klaus Huhn bei einer Buchlesung 2011.JPG|thumb|300px|Huhn at a book-reading in 2011]]\n\n'''Klaus Huhn''' (24 February 1928 \u2013 20 January 2017) was a German sports journalist, writer and sports administrator.<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenKH>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesstiftung-aufarbeitung.de/wer-war-wer-in-der-ddr-%2363%3B-1424.html?ID=3603|author1= Klaus Gallinat |author2= |title=Ullrich, Klaus (eigtl.: Klaus Huhn) * 24.2.1928 Sportjournalist|publisher= Bundesstiftung zur Aufarbeitung der SED-Diktatur: Biographische Datenbanken |language= German|accessdate= 15 July 2015}}</ref> Huhn worked for the [[Germany|East German]] mass-market daily newspaper, ''[[Neues Deutschland]]'', and was chairman of the Sports Journalists Sub-Association within that country's important [[GDR Union of Journalists|Union of Journalists]].\n\nAs a writer he concentrated on the great names from the sporting history of the [[German Democratic Republic|German Democratic Republic (GDR)]], and wrote, more recently, largely for the \"GDR nostalgia\" readership.<ref name=focus>[http://www.focus.de/magazin/archiv/ddr-journalist-klaus-huhn-war-stasi-spitzel_aid_154495.html ''Journalist Klaus Huhn war Stasi-Spitzel.''] In: ''Focus Magazin.'' Nr. 45 (1995), 6. November 1995.</ref>\n\nHe published several books about the cycling legend [[Gustav-Adolf Schur]], and was employed as the [[ghostwriter]] for Schur's autobiography.<ref name=SchurBuchlautReinsch>{{cite web|url=http://www.faz.net/aktuell/feuilleton/buecher/rezension-sachbuch-held-der-beinarbeit-11269834.html|title=Held der Beinarbeit ..... Heilige Sattelzeiten: Gustav-Adolf Schur radelt in seiner Autobiographie \u00fcber H\u00f6lzchen und St\u00f6ckchen |first=Michael | last = Reinsch |publisher=[[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]] (online)|date=20 March 2001|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> The book's objectivity was questioned by one reviewer who described it as \"shameless propaganda\".<ref name=SchurBuchlautReinsch/>\n\n==Life==\nHuhn was born into a [[Communism|Communist]] family, in [[Berlin]], where his father was a clerical worker. Huhn attended [[Gymnasium (Germany)|secondary school]] in Berlin and in [[Saalfeld]].<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenKH/>\n\nIn 1946 he joined the ''[[Deutsche Volkszeitung (1945)|Deutsche Volkszeitung]]'', the [[Zentralorgan|central organ]] of the [[Communist Party of Germany]] (KPD) in the Soviet occupation zone.<ref name=benning>{{citation | first = Kristen | last = Benning | date = 1997 | title = Die Geschichte des SED-Zentralorgans Neues Deutschland von 1946 bis 1949. Die Waffenlieferanten \"im Kampfe gegen die Reaktion und ihre Verwirrungsman\u00f6ver\" |trans-title=The history of SED's official journal ''Neues Deutschland'' from 1946 to 1949: Arms suppliers \"in the struggle against reactionaries and their strategies of distraction\" | language = German | location = M\u00fcnster | publisher = LIT Verlag }}</ref> In 1954 he took a correspondence course in journalism at the [[Leipzig University|Karl Marx University]] in [[Leipzig]] and in 1983 he was at the German College of Physical Culture, also in Leipzig, with a doctorate in [[pedagogy]].\n\nHe died at the age of 88 on 20 January 2017.<ref>[[:de:Wolfgang H\u00fcbner (Journalist)|Wolfgang H\u00fcbner]]: [https://www.neues-deutschland.de/artikel/1039288.eine-grosse-nummer.html ''Eine gro\u00dfe Nummer''], Nachruf in [[Neues Deutschland]], 21 Januar 2017</ref>\n\n==Books==\n*2016 ''Exkursion durch volkseigene Ruinen: Vom Verschwinden einer ganzen Volkswirtschaft'', (\"Excursion Through Nationalized Ruins: the Disappearance of an Entire Economy\"), Edition Berolina, {{ISBN|978-3958-4106-57}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Exkursion-durch-volkseigene-Ruinen-Volkswirtschaft/dp/3958410650|title=Exkursion durch volkseigene Ruinen: Vom Verschwinden einer ganzen Volkswirtschaft|first=Klaus|last=Huhn|publisher=edition berolina|accessdate=21 January 2017|via=Amazon}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Friedrichs, Hanns Joachim (1994), ''Journalists Lives'', Munich, pp. 149 et seq.\n* Huhn, Klaus (2011), \"Auch dem Papst half ich mal aus der Klemme. Episoden eines bewegten Lebens'', Berlin: Edition Ost {{ISBN|978-3-360-01822-9}}.\n* Michael Meyen, Anke Fiedler (ed.) (2010), ''Die Grenze im Kopf. Journalisten in der DDR'', Panama Verlag, {{ISBN|978-3-938714-16-4}}.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huhn, Klaus}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:East German journalists]]\n[[Category:Sports historians]]\n[[Category:German journalists]]\n[[Category:German male journalists]]\n[[Category:People of the Stasi]]\n", "text_old": "{{expand language|topic=|langcode=de|otherarticle=Klaus Huhn|date=July 2015}}\n[[File:Klaus Huhn bei einer Buchlesung 2011.JPG|thumb|300px|Huhn at a book-reading in 2011]]\n\n'''Klaus Huhn''' (24 February 1928 \u2013 20 January 2017) was a German sports journalist, writer and sports administrator.<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenKH>{{cite web|url=http://www.bundesstiftung-aufarbeitung.de/wer-war-wer-in-der-ddr-%2363%3B-1424.html?ID=3603|author1= Klaus Gallinat |author2= |title=Ullrich, Klaus (eigtl.: Klaus Huhn) * 24.2.1928 Sportjournalist|publisher= Bundesstiftung zur Aufarbeitung der SED-Diktatur: Biographische Datenbanken |language= German|accessdate= 15 July 2015}}</ref> Huhn worked for the [[Germany|East German]] mass-market daily newspaper, ''[[Neues Deutschland]]'', and was chairman of the Sports Journalists Sub-Association within that country's important [[GDR Union of Journalists|Union of Journalists]].\n\nAs a writer he concentrated on the great names from the sporting history of the [[German Democratic Republic|German Democratic Republic (GDR)]], and wrote, more recently, largely for the \"GDR nostalgia\" readership.<ref name=focus>[http://www.focus.de/magazin/archiv/ddr-journalist-klaus-huhn-war-stasi-spitzel_aid_154495.html ''Journalist Klaus Huhn war Stasi-Spitzel.''] In: ''Focus Magazin.'' Nr. 45 (1995), 6. November 1995.</ref>\n\nHe published several books about the cycling legend [[Gustav-Adolf Schur]], and was employed as the [[ghostwriter]] for Schur's autobiography.<ref name=SchurBuchlautReinsch>{{cite web|url=http://www.faz.net/aktuell/feuilleton/buecher/rezension-sachbuch-held-der-beinarbeit-11269834.html|title=Held der Beinarbeit ..... Heilige Sattelzeiten: Gustav-Adolf Schur radelt in seiner Autobiographie \u00fcber H\u00f6lzchen und St\u00f6ckchen |first=Michael | last = Reinsch |publisher=[[Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung]] (online)|date=20 March 2001|accessdate=15 July 2015}}</ref> The book's objectivity was questioned by one reviewer who described it as \"shameless propaganda\".<ref name=SchurBuchlautReinsch/>\n\n==Life==\nHuhn was born into a [[Communism|Communist]] family, in [[Berlin]], where his father was a clerical worker. Huhn attended [[Gymnasium (Germany)|secondary school]] in Berlin and in [[Saalfeld]].<ref name=BiographischeDatenbankenKH/>\n\nIn 1946 he joined the ''[[Deutsche Volkszeitung (1945)|Deutsche Volkszeitung]]'', the [[Zentralorgan|central organ]] of the [[Communist Party of Germany]] (KPD) in the Soviet occupation zone.<ref name=benning>{{citation | first = Kristen | last = Benning | date = 1997 | title = Die Geschichte des SED-Zentralorgans Neues Deutschland von 1946 bis 1949. Die Waffenlieferanten \"im Kampfe gegen die Reaktion und ihre Verwirrungsman\u00f6ver\" |trans-title=The history of SED's official journal ''Neues Deutschland'' from 1946 to 1949: Arms suppliers \"in the struggle against reactionaries and their strategies of distraction\" | language = German | location = M\u00fcnster | publisher = LIT Verlag }}</ref> In 1954 he took a correspondence course in journalism at the [[Leipzig University|Karl Marx University]] in [[Leipzig]] and in 1983 he was at the German College of Physical Culture, also in Leipzig, with a doctorate in [[pedagogy]].\n\nHe died at the age of 88 on 20 January 2017.<ref>[[:de:Wolfgang H\u00fcbner (Journalist)|Wolfgang H\u00fcbner]]: [https://www.neues-deutschland.de/artikel/1039288.eine-grosse-nummer.html ''Eine gro\u00dfe Nummer''], Nachruf in [[Neues Deutschland]], 21 Januar 2017</ref>\n\n==Books==\n*2016 ''Exkursion durch volkseigene Ruinen: Vom Verschwinden einer ganzen Volkswirtschaft'', (\"Excursion Through Nationalized Ruins: the Disappearance of an Entire Economy\"), Edition Berolina, {{ISBN|978-3958-4106-57}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.de/Exkursion-durch-volkseigene-Ruinen-Volkswirtschaft/dp/3958410650|title=Exkursion durch volkseigene Ruinen: Vom Verschwinden einer ganzen Volkswirtschaft|first=Klaus|last=Huhn|publisher=edition berolina|accessdate=21 January 2017|via=Amazon}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|35em}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* Friedrichs, Hanns Joachim (1994), ''Journalists Lives'', Munich, pp. 149 et seq.\n* Huhn, Klaus (2011), \"Auch dem Papst half ich mal aus der Klemme. Episoden eines bewegten Lebens'', Berlin: Edition Ost {{ISBN|978-3-360-01822-9}}.\n* Michael Meyen, Anke Fiedler (ed.) (2010), ''Die Grenze im Kopf. Journalisten in der DDR'', Panama Verlag, {{ISBN|978-3-938714-16-4}}.\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Huhn, Klaus}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:East German journalists]]\n[[Category:German journalists]]\n[[Category:German male journalists]]\n[[Category:People of the Stasi]]\n", "name_user": "Vitus Doerfler", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Klaus_Huhn"}
